<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ælvīsyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælvīsyn</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>ælvyst</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ælvesun</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>ælvist</orth></form></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>прясть</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>spin</q></cit></sense><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ælvīsinag</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ælvesujnag</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>шерсть на пряжу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>wool for spinning</q></cit></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_ælvīsyn." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>læg xyzæj axsta kæsægtæ, ūs ta je ʽlvīsinægtæ ælvysta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>муж ловил неводом рыбу, жена пряла свою пряжу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the husband was netting fish; the wife wa spinnig her yarn</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Puškin._Arhau"/><biblScope>3</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>avd xojy se ʽlxujtæ rajstoj, ælvīsinag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>семь сестер взяли свои веретена, пряжу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>seven sisters took their spindles and yarn</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Niger"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>næ wælinʒæbæl æzinæ æz sundak’æ ælviston</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на нашей крыше я вчера пряла шерсть</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>on our roof I spun wool yesterday</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>læg xyzæj axsta kæsægtæ, ūs ta je ʽlvīsinægtæ ælvysta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>муж ловил неводом рыбу, жена пряла свою пряжу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the husband was netting fish; the wife wa spinnig her yarn</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Puškin._Arhau"/><biblScope>3</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>avd xojy se ʽlxujtæ rajstoj, ælvīsinag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>семь сестер взяли свои веретена, пряжу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>seven sisters took their spindles and yarn</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Niger"/><biblScope>94</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>næ wælinʒæbæl æzinæ æz sundak’æ ælviston</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на нашей крыше я вчера пряла шерсть</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>on our roof I spun wool yesterday</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Перестановка из %i*avlīsyn%i (← %i*abi-raiš-%i), ср. такую же метатезу в <xr><ref target="#entry_ælvasyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lvynyn"/></xr> и др. Перебой %ir%i || %il%i перед %ii%i также закономерен, ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_līʒyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_ᵆlǧīvyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lvynyn"/></xr> и др. Как и другие термины ткацкого дела (см. <xr><ref target="#entry_wafyn"/></xr>), относится к иранскому слою; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>riwis-, riwes-</w><gloss><q>прясть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>arw'ī́sna</w><gloss><q>нить</q></gloss></mentioned> (с такой же метатезой, как в ос.!), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>wrēšәl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>brēsaγ, rēsaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>rīštan</w></mentioned>: %ires-%i ‘прясть’ (сюда же относят <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>ābrēšum</w><gloss><q>шелк</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/><w>rēsa</w><gloss><q>пряжа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>rēš- rišati</w><gloss><q>рвать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>щипать</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_lystæg"/></xr> | %ilistæg%i ‘мелкий’ <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl> производит от этого же корня. Ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_wafyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_nyvændyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lxuj"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_wædært"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>III 159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_MSL"><biblScope>XX 10</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Metathesis from %i*avlīsyn%i (← %i*abi-raiš-%i), cf. the same metathesis in <xr><ref target="#entry_ælvasyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lvynyn"/></xr> etc. The alternation %ir%i || %il%i before %ii%i is also regular, cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_līʒyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_ᵆlǧīvyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lvynyn"/></xr> etc. Like other weaving terms (see <xr><ref target="#entry_wafyn"/></xr>), it is Iranian; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>riwis-, riwes-</w><gloss><q>spin</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>arw'ī́sna</w><gloss><q>thread</q></gloss></mentioned> (with the same metathesis as in Ossetic!), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>wrēšәl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>brēsaγ, rēsaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>rīštan</w></mentioned>: %ires-%i ‘spin’ (to here also concerns <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>ābrēšum</w><gloss><q>silk</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/><w>rēsa</w><gloss><q>yarn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>rēš- rišati</w><gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>pinch</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_lystæg"/></xr> | %ilistæg%i ‘small’ <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl> traces back to the same root. Cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_wafyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_nyvændyn"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_lxuj"/></xr>, <xr><ref target="#entry_wædært"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>III 159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_MSL"><biblScope>XX 10</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>